  "local_port": 49198,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I get a OBC NCL Certificate?",
  "response": "To obtain an **OBC Non-Creamy Layer (NCL) Certificate**, you need to follow a specific process as per the guidelines provided by the Government of India. The OBC NCL Certificate is issued to individuals belonging to the **Other Backward Classes (OBC)** who do not fall under the \"creamy layer\" category. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Get an OBC NCL Certificate**\n\n1. **Check Eligibility**:\n   - Your family must belong to the OBC category as per the Central or State Government list.\n   - Your family income should be below the threshold limit (currently \u20b98 lakhs per annum) to qualify as Non-Creamy Layer.\n\n2. **Gather Required Documents**:\n   - Proof of identity (Aadhaar card, PAN card, voter ID, etc.).\n   - Proof of residence (ration card, electricity bill, etc.).\n   - Income certificate (issued by a competent authority like a Tehsildar).\n   - Caste certificate (if already issued).\n   - Affidavit (if required by the issuing authority).\n   - Passport-sized photographs.\n   - School/college records (for self or parents, if applicable).\n\n3. **Application Form**:\n   - Obtain the application form for the OBC NCL Certificate from the local revenue office (Tehsil/Taluka office), SDM office, or online portal of your state government (if available).\n   - Fill the form with accurate details.\n\n4. **Submit the Application**:\n   - Submit the filled application form along with the required documents to the designated authority (Tehsildar, SDM, or District Magistrate).\n   - Pay the prescribed fee, if applicable.\n\n5. **Verification Process**:\n   - The authorities will verify your documents and conduct an inquiry to confirm your eligibility.\n   - This may include a visit to your residence or workplace.\n\n6. **Certificate Issuance**:\n   - Once the verification is complete, the OBC NCL Certificate will be issued.\n   - The certificate is usually issued within 15\u201330 days, depending on the state and authority.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**:\n- The OBC NCL Certificate is valid only if it is issued by a competent authority.\n- The certificate is essential for availing reservations in government jobs, educational institutions, and other schemes.\n- If you already have an OBC certificate, you can apply for the NCL Certificate separately by providing income proof.\n\n---\n\n### **Online Application (if available)**:\nSome states provide online portals to apply for the OBC NCL Certificate. For example:\n- Visit the official website of your state\u2019s Backward Classes Welfare Department or Revenue Department.\n- Register and fill out the online application form.\n- Upload the required documents and submit the application.\n- Track the application status online.\n\n---\n\nIf you need further assistance, contact your local Tehsil office or the Backward Classes Welfare Department in your state.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
